This is Perl module Catalyst::Plugin::Lazy::Encoding.

INSTALLATION

Catalyst::Plugin::Lazy::Encoding installation is straightforward. If your CPAN shell is set up,
you should just be able to do

    % cpan Catalyst::Plugin::Lazy::Encoding

Download it, unpack it, then build it as per the usual:

    % perl Makefile.PL
    % make && make test

Then install it:

    % make install

DOCUMENTATION

Catalyst::Plugin::Lazy::Encoding documentation is available as in POD. So you can do:

    % perldoc Catalyst::Plugin::Lazy::Encoding

to read the documentation online with your favorite pager.

